page.title: 10Ecology (continued)
page.content:
The becks and tarns support five kinds of fish, and the insect life ranges from the annoying midges to the lovely butterflies. The multiplicity of flora is due to the varied habitat and one finds wild daffodils, bluebells, wild orchids and waterlilies. Birds which are indiginous to the area vary from the wee firecrest at 3.5 inches to the buzzard with a wingspan of 4.5 feet. Migrant and resident types include divers, grebes, heron, waterfowl, birds of prey, gamebirds and waders. The cuckoo may often be heard and there are numerous song and garden birds.
The whole area is one of outstanding natural beauty.
